  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CSR Facility 2015: Ulandssekretariatet. Promotion of a rights-based inclusive and business sustainable CSR approach in the Philippines.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of the project is to promote business responsibility and thus contribute to improved working and living conditions of the workers in the Philippines. The project is targeting the government as well as existing and potential enterprises in the Philippines - including Danish Companies and is based on utilising CSR as a tool to improve productivity and competitiveness, and ensure decent work on the labour market in the Philippines. The project supports capacity building of PELSPI to put focus on CSR nationally and regionally in ASEAN and to put focus on the integration of labour rights in the development of CSR guidelines in the plastic industry as well as establish Works Councils in local workplaces to monitor the development and implementation of these CSR guidelines in companies in the plastic industry.</narrative>
  </description>
